### Common Mistakes (Self-Diagnostic)

| Mistake | Detection | Fix |
|---------|-----------|-----|
| Color on wrong element | Check which text actually has the accent color | Re-extract with precise element targeting |
| Font weight wrong | Serif fonts often look bolder at 400 | Note visual weight vs actual weight |
| Cards missing borders | Divs may have subtle borders not visible in overview | Inspect individual card elements |
| Line heights blank | Rushed extraction | Re-run DevTools, force lineHeight measurement |
| Icons missed | Only looked at text elements | Search for `svg`, `img`, `[class*="icon"]` |
| Nav CTA missed | Focused on main content only | Always scan nav/header separately |

---

> **Note on Color Values:** Browser DevTools returns colors as RGB (e.g., `rgb(30, 79, 138)`). Convert to HEX for CSS:
> ```python
> import re
> def rgb_to_hex(rgb_str):
>     nums = re.findall(r'\d+', rgb_str)
>     if len(nums) >= 3:
>         return f"#{int(nums[0]):02x}{int(nums[1]):02x}{int(nums[2]):02x}">     return rgb_str
> # Example: rgb(30, 79, 138) → #1e4f8a
> ```

