### CSS Best Practices

**Do NOT use `!important`:**
- Using `!important` overrides Elementor's visual controls
- Users won't be able to edit font sizes, colors, or backgrounds via the UI
- Build CSS without `!important` so Elementor controls work normally

**Example (correct):**
```css
.elementor-element-aeb44c8 {
    background-color: #1E4F8A;
    min-height: 100vh;
}
.elementor-element-94c078c .elementor-heading-title {
    font-size: 48px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #FFFFFF;
}
```

**If you need stronger specificity:**
- Use more specific selectors (`.elementor-element-{ID} .elementor-widget-container h2`)
- Target the specific Elementor classes instead of adding `!important`

