## Critical Notes

### Widget Type Field Mapping

| Widget Type | Field Name | Example |
|-------------|------------|---------|
| heading | `title` | `item['settings']['title'] = 'Headline'` |
| text-editor | `editor` | `item['settings']['editor'] = '<p>Body text</p>'` |
| button | `text` | `item['settings']['text'] = 'Click Me'` |
| image | `url`, `alt` | `item['settings']['url'] = 'image.jpg'` |

### SSH Commands Reference

```bash
# SSH with password (non-interactive)
sshpass -p "$PASSWORD" ssh -o StrictHostKeyChecking=no user@host "command"

# WP-CLI database query
wp db query "SELECT meta_value FROM wp_postmeta WHERE post_id = 606 AND meta_key = '_elementor_data'"

# WP-CLI update post meta
wp post meta update 606 _elementor_data --format=json < /tmp/data.json

# Clear Elementor cache
wp elementor flush-css
wp cache flush
```

### Common Issues

**Permission denied on SSH:**
- Install `sshpass` if not available: `apt-get install sshpass`
- Verify credentials in MEMORY.md
- Check if SSH key auth is required instead

**Changes not showing on frontend:**
- Clear Elementor CSS cache: `wp elementor flush-css`
- Clear WordPress cache: `wp cache flush`
- Clear browser cache (add `?nocache=1` to URL)

**Widget content not updating:**
- Verify widget ID matches exactly (case-sensitive)
- Check widget type and use correct field name
- Ensure JSON is valid before pushing

